		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=153066"><span class="">Zwingli</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />89 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=1086265608335669660;page=1;howmany=50#1086306159999909261"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Depends on how you look at it... <br /> <br />Chain healing can mean constantly hitting your heal one after the other on your groups tank. Thats the simple answer and isnt what you are asking. <br /> <br />More than likely you are asking about a &quot;chain&quot; of clerics healing on a raid. Basically you have 3+ clerics casting Complete Heal in a row. Each generally has a hotkey setup that says in the raid channel what their number is in the &quot;chain&quot;. So you have cleric #1 cast CH, cleric #2 waits a predetermined amount of time and then hits CH then cleric #3 and so on til the last cleric in the chain hits CH. Then you start back at cleric #1 and keep going until the mob is dead. For example if you had 6 clerics with a 4 second delay, each cleric will wait 4 seconds after the cleric before them in the chain hit CH and then they would hit their hotkey. The whole reason is some boss mobs hit fast and hard and a tank will die in a matter of seconds. With a rotation you have a &quot;chain&quot; of clerics hitting the tank with CH every few seconds. If each cleric hit nothing but fast heals you may run out of mana before the mob is dead and the raid wipes.   <br /> <br />Lets say for example I was the 4th cleric in a 6 cleric rotation, my hotkey would look something like this. <br /> <br /> <br />/2 44444444 CH %t 44444444   <br />/cast 6 (6 is my gem slot for my CH spell)  <br />/cast 6 (I repeat this in case of fizzles) <br />/cast 6 <br />/cast 6 <br /> <br />---- I put /2 because that is the our guild cleric channel so we dont spam the entire raid with CH messages. But you can use /rs or /gu or whatever your particular group uses. <br /> <br />Good luck  <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Zwingli Integritous 65 Archon of Brell <br />Fachkin             58 Conjurer <br />Sassafraas          56 Heretic <br />Xegony</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
