<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I woulnd't recommend using the pause for a few reasons.  <br /> <br />1) You don't want alot of extra text in the heal channel since it can get in the way. If cleric Joe Blow is asking for a twitch or posting his mana level, and cleric NEWB has a heal message something like this: (I am now completely healing &lt;&lt;&lt; %T &gt;&gt;&gt; this is a 10 second cast so hold on to your horses while I try and get this thing to land!!), chances are that alot of important text can get missed if someone else was to follow along with a similar message. We use a standard and simple format for our rotation macros: <br />/cast 1 <br />/2 CH to Mulak -- MARTHANA next <br />/cast 1 <br />blank <br />/cast 1 <br /> <br />The capital letters will bring assist you in seeing who is next. If you notice, we start our casting first, and then the message. The heal is the priority, second is the message. Start the cast and then let them know who is next. <br /> <br />2)Dont have a message to prompt the other cleric, it is their responsabilty to make sure they are on time with thier heal. This is not an exact science, and shouldn't be looked at as such. If a cleric in your rotation can't count to 4 or what ever the pause is, you should seek to replace them. Once again you are generating text spam that is not needed in the chat. Necrocs have to see the request for the twitch in order for them to get it to you. <br /> <br />I hope this helps out and I was by no means trying to flame, just offering a tried and true method we use on my server.</p>
