<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I guess everyone has thier opinions on it. I'll comment on the problems as I see them in others suggestions. <br /> #1: The pause should always be a part of the hotkey IMO. I have never seen it work without it in there. Lag has never been a big issue and if you are laggy then I think it's your responsibility to state this and not be in chains. The pause doesn't necesarily have to be stated in the channel and by the time you are doing chains then you should have your chat boxes set up appropriatly. <br />#2: IMO the cast should be the first thing in the hot key. Then the heal meassage and the second cast following this. There are times if you put the casts directly one after the other other that lag will mess up the &quot;fizzle catch&quot; cast and then it will simply skip over the next cast. <br />#3 I feel that you should always prompt the next cleric. There are simply too many times that a mob can add, the chain get a little buggered up and without the prompts and pauses in the hotkeys it can be a mass of confusion getting back on track. If your tank isn't geared to the nines or is on one of the GoD mobs this can end up dropping an entire raid. <br />If the chain isn't rock solid then alot of times it can kill a raid. Without the above stated things I think you are just setting it up for failure. Especially on a mobs like agnaar, Terris Thule or Saryrn (to name a few) where mobs are popping during fights and that usually last a little while.</p>
