<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Pthhhh... <br /> <br />First I always have a window designated to cleric channels... and that is what I am paying attention to if I am in a chain... second we keep our messages short as well and containing useful info... sometimes we number the clerics in the chain so if one drops or lds  the others can pick up their spot fast ... so the initial tell would go something like this <br /> <br />/2 (4)---- CH INC TO %T ------(10) <br /> <br />where: <br />2= cleric channel <br />4= the number this cleric is in the order <br />10= the delay <br /> <br />Delays is soooooo important as far as I'm concerned... it keeps the chain as exact as it can be... it helps prevent excess mana use and assures that the CH lands in pretty precise intervals...and if you use a Chain channel and keep it in a seperate window spam is not an issue...  <br /> <br />As far as I am concerned the pause should not be done without... the negatives are minimal and unimportant. <br /> <br /></p>
