<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>In my past guild I was the assistant cleric class leader and we used this format. <br /> <br />/pause 15   This was a 1.5sec pause but was changed as needed.  <br />/cast 2     Spell gem slot number where you have c-healing.  <br />/pause 5    This is a fizzle reset pause. If first fizzle This one would save it. <br />/cast 2      Recast in case of fizzle <br />/1 ---( 1 )--- Ch to %t ---( 1 )---  <br /> <br />This was set up to minimise spam for the quick chain. Each cleric was given a number at beginning of raid and that hot key saved for next raid. Change people only as needed and there will be vary little setup for the chain. Soon as you see the number before you then you can cast, If down right you can time your own cast just by watching the numbers scroll. I never has a problem out of this way.  <br />  <br />I will point out the /pause 5. 1/2 second pause for fizzle to reset and the backup cast command.  <br /> <br /></p>
